text:
Jessa Marie Certifeco the Bill was passed sa House of Representatives on its third and final reading. Thereafter, the Bill goes to the Senate for another round of reading and deliberations. If the Senate so happens to have its own version of the Bill and it has passed their third and final reading, a bi-partisan committee composed of members of both houses will be formed to iron out the final version of the Bill.

Once done, it goes to the President to be signed into law.

Should the President veto the bill either in its entirety or just portions of it, Congress may opt not to touch their final version. After a short period of time, it will automatically lapse into law.

Thereafter, the Department of Justice will have to write out an Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) and publish the same sa Official Gazette. After a period of 30 days (I think), then the law is ready for implementation.

The Supreme Court, the Philippine Law Center, the Department of Justice, and the Integrated Bar of the Philippines will then have to draw up a syllabus and training content to train lawyers and judges about this new law.

So, medyo matagal tagal pa rin before we can see the first cases to be filed in court. But we're getting there, eventually.

Corsino Paranas III saan po sinabi ni Jesus na hindi pwedeng mag asawang muli ang isang tao, after na hiwalayan nya ang asawa nya na nagtaksil sa kanya?

Malinaw naman na sinabi ni Jesus na hindi pwedeng hiwalayan ng tao ang asawa nya sa anumang kadahilanan maliban sa pakikiapid o adultery, still may ground po ng paghihiwalay, o divorce,
Kung ang isang tao ay divorce na, sya ay legally free man o woman, sa batas ng tao at sa mata ng Dios malaya na sya

So saan po nasabi ni Jesus na hindi na pwede magasawa ang isang malayang tao?

Pakibasa po ang Deuteronomy 24:1-4,

Ang pagkaintindi ko po kc jan, Kung ang nakiapid nga na babae ay pwede mag asawa sa iba after sya hiwalayan ng lalaki na una nya asawa wag lang sya babalik sa unang asawa, 
Un pa kayang lalaki na di naman nagkasala sa kanilang pagsasama hindi pwede mag asawa ng iba?

Wala po kc ako nabasa na sinabi ni Jesus n hindi pwede magasawa muli ang isang taong nakipahiwalay sa kanyang asawang nangaliwa.

text:
Vanie Rabanillo  the Bill was passed sa House of Representatives on its third and final reading. Thereafter, the Bill goes to the Senate for another round of reading and deliberations. If the Senate so happens to have its own version of the Bill and it has passed their third and final reading, a bi-partisan committee composed of members of both houses will be formed to iron out the final version of the Bill.

Once done, it goes to the President to be signed into law.

Should the President veto the bill either in its entirety or just portions of it, Congress may opt not to touch their final version. After a short period of time, it will automatically lapse into law.

Thereafter, the Department of Justice will have to write out an Implementing Rules and Regulations (IRR) and publish the same sa Official Gazette. After a period of 30 days (I think), then the law is ready for implementation.

The Supreme Court, the Philippine Law Center, the Department of Justice, and the Integrated Bar of the Philippines will then have to draw up a syllabus and training content to train lawyers and judges about this new law.

So, medyo matagal tagal pa rin before we can see the first cases to be filed in court. But we're getting there, eventually.

text:
Kaya nga po may grounds ang divorce eh, may mga reason lang na papayagan, at un ang pinagaaralan kung dapat ba iapproved

Hindi po kasama dito ang slight na trials ng pagsasama bilang magasawa, iaassess pa rin yan, kung iapproved ba ang case un,

Ang grounds ng divorce ay nakatutok sa mga rason na hindi na talaga maresolba, 
Kesa humantong sa extreme situation, mabuti pa maghiwalay na, 

Kasama po talaga ang Dios kc mababasa rin sa Bible na kalooban nya rin na may divorce, basahin nyo nalang po, 
Ang divorce ay hindi para sirain ang pagsasama 
It's a solution for dead marriages.

text:
Agcanas Junel kaya nga po may grounds eh, hindi bastabasta ang pagfile, kelangan patunayan na victim sya,
Nasa mag asawa na kung paano nila poprotektahan ang kanilang pagsasama, mas matatakot pa nga gumawa ng kasalanan ang isa kung ayaw nila hiwalayan cla kc may divorce, 
Kahit saang bansa na legal ang divorce ka magpunta kung strong kau pareho, hindi nyo kailangan ang divorce, 
Kc ngaun kahit wala pa divorce marami na ang nahuhulog sa tukso. Un ang realidad ng buhay.

Kung babaero at lalakero ang isa, pinatunayan nya lang na hindi sya karapatdapat sa babae o lalaking pinakasalan nya. Deserve ng partner nya ng bagong makakasama sa buhay na hindi sya bibigyan ng sama ng loob, isang masaya at payapang pagsasama, ung ang gusto ng Dios,
Hindi ang kasal nga pero dinudungisan ng isa, at ayaw nya lang pakawalan ang partner nya dahil kasal, 
It's unfair.

Then nakikita pa ng mga anak kung paano tratuhin ang ina o ama, 
Not a very good example.
Kesa magkapatayan pa, it is better to have a legal procedure to part ways,
With both rights especially the children being considered.

katulad nyan, pede b n mga GUNGGONG lang ang sakop nyan tapos wag nman lahatin para s mga walang kabalak-balak. parang lahat kasi ngayon pede n mahulog s tukso.
